The paper focuses on the development of a layered architecture for secure big data processing in untrusted cloud environments. This involves the use of novel security mechanisms present in recent commodity CPUs, such as Intel's Software Guard Extensions (SGX). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
